<% content_for :title do %>Captain AI | <%= installation_brand_name %> User Guide<% end %>
<% content_for :meta_description do %>
  Set up Captain assistants, documents, FAQs, and Copilot in <%= installation_brand_name %> for AI-assisted customer support.
<% end %>

<h1>Captain AI</h1>
<p class="lead">
  Captain helps your team answer customers faster using AI trained on your documents and conversation history.
  Admins configure Captain; agents use <strong>Copilot</strong> inside conversations.
</p>

<h2>Is Captain available?</h2>
<p>
  Captain may not appear on every installation or plan. If you do not see <strong>Captain</strong> in the left sidebar,
  contact your workspace operator or upgrade if Captain is limited to paid tiers on your host.
</p>

<h2>Captain vs Copilot vs bots</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Captain</strong> — AI layer with assistants, documents, FAQs, and scenarios (admin-managed)</li>
  <li><strong>Copilot</strong> — sidebar inside a conversation that drafts replies for agents to review and send</li>
  <li><strong>Agent bots</strong> — webhook integrations under <strong>Settings → Bots</strong> that POST events to your own server (separate from Captain)</li>
</ul>

<h2>Admin setup overview</h2>
<ol>
  <li>Open <strong>Captain</strong> in the sidebar.</li>
  <li>Create or select an <strong>assistant</strong> for your workspace.</li>
  <li>Add <strong>Documents</strong> (help articles, PDFs, URLs) the assistant can learn from.</li>
  <li>Review <strong>FAQs</strong> Captain suggests from past conversations; approve useful ones.</li>
  <li>Attach the assistant to inboxes under <strong>Captain → Inboxes</strong>.</li>
  <li>Test in <strong>Playground</strong> before going live with customers.</li>
</ol>

<h2>Documents</h2>
<p>
  Documents are your knowledge source. Connect your help center, upload files, or add URLs Captain should use when answering.
  Better documents produce better suggestions. Keep content up to date when products or policies change.
</p>

<h2>FAQs (responses)</h2>
<p>
  Captain can surface frequently asked questions from real conversations.
  Admins review pending FAQs and approve or reject them so only accurate answers are used.
</p>

<h2>Scenarios and guidelines</h2>
<p>
  Under <strong>Captain → Settings</strong> you can define guidelines and guardrails: tone, topics to avoid,
  when to hand off to a human, and scenario-specific behavior. Use these to keep replies on-brand and safe.
</p>

<h2>Tools (if enabled)</h2>
<p>
  Captain Tools let the assistant call approved actions (for example looking up order status) during a conversation.
  Availability depends on your plan and installation configuration.
</p>

<h2>Using Copilot as an agent</h2>
<ol>
  <li>Open a customer conversation.</li>
  <li>Open the <strong>Copilot</strong> panel in the sidebar.</li>
  <li>Ask for a draft reply or summary based on the thread.</li>
  <li><strong>Always review</strong> the suggestion before sending — edit or discard as needed.</li>
</ol>
<p>
  Copilot assists agents; it does not replace human judgment for sensitive, legal, or high-stakes cases.
</p>

<h2>Captain credits and limits</h2>
<p>
  Some hosts meter Captain usage (responses, documents, or credits). If you see limit warnings in the app,
  reduce automated usage, upgrade your plan, or contact your operator.
</p>

<h2>Best practices</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Start with one inbox and a small document set, then expand</li>
  <li>Approve FAQs only when answers are verified</li>
  <li>Set clear handoff rules for billing, refunds, and complaints</li>
  <li>Re-test in Playground after changing documents or guidelines</li>
</ul>

